nodes.bodyText:
Using CompositeFuture in the return type is not very nice, because it means callers of this method need to know what the elements of the composite are, and CompositeFuture is not type safe. I think it would be much nicer to declare a class which holds the metrics cm and the logging cm, like this:
public class MetricsAndLoggingCm {
    public ConfigMap metricsCm;
    public ConfigMap loggingCm;
    MetricsAndLoggingCm(ConfigMap metricsCm, ConfigMap loggingCm) {
        // ...
    }
}
and have this method return a Future<MetricsAndLoggingCm> (by doing map on the result of the join). That way it's all much more self-describing.

